Hey, look this workaround. Maybe it can help to solve hide "letter by letter" on overflow before the correct solution:

## Steps to do
1. Create a `Text` to each letter;
2. Include all the `Text` in a `Row`;
3. Get the `Row` rect;
4. Get each `Text` rect;
5. Validate if the `Text` rect is in the `Row` rect and, case isn't in the rect, hide it;

## I found this problems
1. The character spacing is little bigger comparing with simple `Text` widget;
2. The `Row` is duplicated to get the row size after the first frame is rendered;

I tried to implement it in this package: [text_helpers](https://pub.dev/packages/text_helpers)

