That's a terribly inefficient way of doing things. Just have a look at the [underlying code for the `Text` widget](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/2f73173c36f806c7f30e705a90722082f85a2c8b/packages/flutter/lib/src/widgets/text.dart#L520), and you'll see why.

The workaround does not seem to work for multi-byte characters. I tried Chinese characters but the text has white space at the end. You can try the following sample code.

Some text does not have white space at the end (You can see it at the bottom of the text in the following sample). I believe this is the expected behavior.

Are there any solutions?

